CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 21, 1973, pg. 10 reads: "Wee Prize Winners - Trinity AME Church, Wylie Ave. at Francis St., was the scene of the recent Baby Contest and Hostess Party which preceded the 15th Annual AIO State Grand Lodge Session, and the wee winners seem none the worse after the battle. Mrs. Irene Mitchell, left, presents the award to the first place winner, Baby Colette Duboise, resting in the arms of her Daddy, while Mother Duboise looks on from the right.  baby Thomas Chatman, Jr., second prize winner, seems to question the whole procedure, as he rests in the soft embrace of his mother, Mrs. Delores Chatman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Irene Mitchell, presenting first place award to Colette Duboise, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Duboise, while Delores Chatman holding son Thomas Chatman, Jr. looks on, in Trinity AME Church for baby contest, another version
